Senator Dino Melaye, representing Kogi West,  has reacted to the nullification of his election by the Court of Appeal sitting in Abuja on Friday, urging his teeming supporters not to lose any hope. The appellate court sitting in Abuja, on Friday, nullified the Senator’s election and ordered a fresh election for the senatorial zone. In a tweet on his twitter handle (@dino_melaye ), Melaye gave praise to God. “I just lost my election at the Appeal Court and Fresh election ordered. In all things, I give God the Praise. He who started a good thing will definitely complete it. I ask my supporters to be law-abiding as we shall always overcome. To God be the Glory,” Melaye twitted.  Felix Omohomhion, Abuja